<OUTPUT_TEXT>Dear Staff,

As we approach the new school year, I want to remind everyone of the importance of enforcing administration policies and rules governing our students. Consistency in upholding these guidelines is crucial in maintaining a safe and productive learning environment for all.

Please familiarize yourselves with the school's policies on behavior, dress code, attendance, and any other relevant rules. It is our collective responsibility to ensure that students adhere to these regulations at all times.

If you encounter any issues or violations, please address them promptly and in accordance with the established protocols. By consistently enforcing the rules, we can help instill a sense of discipline and respect among our students.

Thank you for your cooperation in upholding our administration policies. Together, we can create a positive and supportive school community for our students to thrive.

Best regards,

[Your Name]
Senior Elementary School Teacher</OUTPUT_TEXT>
